    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tubes of various dimensions used to dispense consecrated wine, or wine and bread, at communion. Used occasionally up until the sixteenth century; use contintued by the Pope and his deacons up until the Second Vatican Council (1962-1965) during papal Masses.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
